assessment_details.task_description:
The aim of this assessment task is to increase the students's knowledge across the breadth of the Course content. This is achieved by a combination of:

pre-reading of the specified chapter of the text (Lawrence and Weber, 2014);

completion of the Learning Unit pro forma for that week;

pre-reading of the set Case Study;

active discussion of the case in the class; and

making notes in the Tutorial case discussion pro forma for that case study.

Assessment of the mark awarded to the individual student is based upon two papers submitted by the individual student each week, namely:

the completed Learning Unit pro forma for that week; and

the completed Case study discussion paper.
